==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flannel flower
<hw>Flan"nel flow`er</hw>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
common mullein.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A Brazilian apocynaceous vine
(<spn>Macrosiphonia longiflora</spn>) having woolly leaves.</def>
<sd>(c)</sd> <def>An umbelliferous Australian flower (<spn>Actinotus
helianthi</spn>), often erroneously thought to be composite. The
involucre looks as if cut out of white flannel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flannen</ent>⟦br⟧
